definition.value: An EC 3.2.1.* (glycosidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of glucosylceramidase (EC 3.2.1.45).
An EC 3.2.1.* (glycosidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of sucrose alpha-glucosidase (EC 3.2.1.48).
An EC 3.2.1.* (glycosidase) inhibitor that inhibits the action of sucrose oligo-1,6-glucosidase (EC 3.2.1.10).
A conduritol epoxide resulting from the formal epoxidation of the double bond of (+)-conduritol B.
A conduritol epoxide resulting from the formal epoxidation of the double bond of (-)-conduritol B.
An epoxide resulting from the epoxidation of the double bond of a conduritol.
An acyclic diterpene glycoside consisting of a 20-hydroxygeranyllinalool skeleton conjugated to two disaccharide units at C-3 and C-20.
An oxysterol that is the 22R-hydroxy derivative of cholesterol.
A monocarboxylic acid comprised of hexanoic acid substituted on C-6 by a 4-[(2S)-2-(methylamino)propyl]phenyl group.
An EC 3.2.1.* (glycosidase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of alpha-glucosidase (EC 3.2.1.20).
An acyclic diterpene glycoside consisting of a 20-hydroxygeranyllinalool skeleton conjugated to a glucosyl residue at C-20 and a rhamnosylglucosyl moiety at C-3.
A polyprenyl glycosyl phosphate consisting of beta-D-galactofuranosyl-(1->4)-alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine attached at the 1-position to trans,octacis-decaprenyl phosphate.
An acyclic diterpene glycoside consisting of a 20-hydroxygeranyllinalool skeleton conjugated to a malonylglucosyl residue at C-20 and a rhamnosylglucosyl moiety at C-3.
An acyclic diterpene glycoside consisting of a 20-hydroxygeranyllinalool skeleton conjugated to a malonylglucosyl residue at C-20 and a rhamnosyl(malonyl)glucosyl moiety at C-3.
A lignan that is tetrahydrofuran substituted at positions 2, 3 and 4 by 4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl, hydroxymethyl and 4-hydroxy-3-methoxybenzyl groups respectively (the 2R,3S,4S-diastereomer).
An enantiomer of pinoresinol having (-)-1R,3aS,4R,6aS-configuration.
A lignan that is tetrahydrofuran substituted at positions 2, 3 and 4 by 4-hydroxy-3-methoxyphenyl, hydroxymethyl and 4-hydroxy-3-methoxybenzyl groups respectively (the 2S,3R,4R-diastereomer).
An enantiomer of secoisolariciresinol having (+)-(2S,3S)-configuration.
An amino acid zwitterion arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of 4-(3-methylbut-2-enyl)-L-abrine.
A dipeptide that is the N-acetyl derivative of carnosine.
A lignan that is butane-1,4-diol in which the 2 and 3 positions are substituted by 4-hydroxy-3-methoxybenzyl groups
A cyclic monoterpene ketone that is 2,6,6-trimethylcyclohexa-1,3-diene substituted at position 1 by a crotonoyl group.
A terpene ketone in which an (E,E)-farnesyl group is bonded to one of the alpha-methyls of acetone.
A polyprenyl glycosyl phosphate consisting of alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine attached at the 1-position to trans,octacis-decaprenyl phosphate.
A monocarboxylic acid that is propanoic acid substituted at C-3 by a 2-methoxyethoxy group.
A monocarboxylic acid that is propanoic acid substituted at C-2 by a 2-methoxyethoxy group.

A polyprenyl glycosyl phosphate consisting of beta-D-galactofuranosyl-(1->5)-beta-D-galactofuranosyl-(1->4)-alpha-L-rhamnosyl-(1->3)-N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine attached at the 1-position to trans,octacis-decaprenyl phosphate.
A 4-hydroxyproline substituted at N-1 by an ethoxycarbonyl group.
An epoxide resulting from the formal epoxidation of the double bond between positions 2 and 3 of geranial.
A 4-hydroxyproline substituted at N-1 by an methoxyacetyl group.
An unsaturated fatty acid anion that is the conjugate base of geranic acid, obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
An acyl-CoA oxoanion arising from deprotonation of phosphate, diphosphate and carboxylic acid functions of 2,3-dehydroadipyl-CoA.
A beta-diketone that is curcumin in which one of the double bonds has been reduced to a single bond.
A beta-diketone that is curcumin in which both of the double bonds have been reduced to single bonds.
A polyunsaturated fatty acid that is octa-2,6-dienoic acid bearing two methyl substituents at positions 3 and 7 (the 2E-isomer).
A diketone in which the two keto groups are separated by a single carbon atom.
An apo carotenoid monoterpenoid that is alpha-ionone with a hydroxy substituent at position 3.
An EC 2.5.1.* (non-methyl-alkyl or aryl transferase) inhibitor that interferes with the action of protein geranylgeranyltransferase type I (EC 2.5.1.59).
An inhibitor of HIV-1 integrase, an enzyme required for the integration of the genetic material of the retrovirus into the DNA of the infected cells.

A member of the class of 2,5-diketopiperazines that is piperazine-2,5-dione in which one hydrogen at position 3 and one hydrogen at position 6 are replaced by isobutyl groups (the 3S,6S-diastereomer).
A carbohydrate acid that is heptanoic acid substituted by hydroxy groups at C-2, C-3, C-4, C-5, C-6, and C-7.
An organic heterotricyclic compound that is [1,2,4]triazolo[3,4-f][1,6]naphthyridin-3(2H)-one substituted at positions 8 and 9 respectively by 4-(1-aminocyclobutyl)phenyl and phenyl groups.
A phospholipid consisting of 1,1-dimethylpiperidinium-4-yl hydrogen phosphate in which the hydrogen is replaced by a stearyl (octadecyl) group.
Any 1,4-benzoquinone carrying a single hydroxy substituent.

A zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of any lysophosphatidylethanolamine. The structure is depicted in the image where R(1) = acyl, R(2) = H or where R(1) = H, R(2) = acyl.

An amino oligosaccharide that is a branched decasaccharide derivative comprised of a mannose residue to which is linked an N-acetylgalactosaminyl residue at O-2, a glucosyl residue at O-3 and a beta-D-QuiN4Fm-(1->4)-alpha-D-GalNAcAN-(1->4)-alpha-D-GalNAcAN-(1->3)-beta-D-QuiNAc tetrasaccharide chain at O-4, all linked to an [alpha-D-Glc-(1->2)]-alpha-D-Man-(1->5)-alpha-Kdo branched trisaccharide unit.
